<text id="02-output-contract" title="Spring Boot JUnit Testing Output Contract" version="1.1.0" est_tokens="900" depth="essential">
  <summary>JSON Schema for the test-plan manifest this methodology produces. Validator enforces required keys + per-field constraints.</summary>

  <section title="Schema">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
  "$id": "https://faion.net/schemas/java-junit-testing.json",
  "type": "object",
  "required": ["module", "framework", "test_classes", "coverage", "uses_testcontainers", "springboottest_count"],
  "properties": {
    "module": {"type": "string", "minLength": 1},
    "framework": {"const": "junit5"},
    "test_classes": {
      "type": "array",
      "minItems": 1,
      "items": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["name", "layer", "slice_annotation", "test_count"],
        "properties": {
          "name": {"type": "string", "pattern": "Test$"},
          "layer": {"enum": ["controller", "service", "repository", "integration"]},
          "slice_annotation": {"enum": ["@WebMvcTest", "@ExtendWith(MockitoExtension.class)", "@DataJpaTest", "@SpringBootTest"]},
          "test_count": {"type": "integer", "minimum": 1}
        }
      }
    },
    "coverage": {
      "type": "object",
      "required": ["line", "branch", "tool", "gate_enforced_in_ci"],
      "properties": {
        "line": {"type": "number", "minimum": 70},
        "branch": {"type": "number", "minimum": 60},
        "tool": {"const": "jacoco"},
        "gate_enforced_in_ci": {"type": "boolean", "const": true}
      }
    },
    "uses_testcontainers": {"type": "boolean", "const": true},
    "springboottest_count": {"type": "integer", "maximum": 1},
    "forbidden_patterns_found": {"type": "array", "items": {"type": "string"}, "maxItems": 0}
  }
}
]]></code>
  </section>

  <example valid="true">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "module": "billing-service",
  "framework": "junit5",
  "test_classes": [
    {"name": "UserControllerTest", "layer": "controller", "slice_annotation": "@WebMvcTest", "test_count": 8},
    {"name": "UserServiceTest", "layer": "service", "slice_annotation": "@ExtendWith(MockitoExtension.class)", "test_count": 14},
    {"name": "UserRepositoryTest", "layer": "repository", "slice_annotation": "@DataJpaTest", "test_count": 6},
    {"name": "BillingApiIT", "layer": "integration", "slice_annotation": "@SpringBootTest", "test_count": 4}
  ],
  "coverage": {"line": 78.4, "branch": 64.2, "tool": "jacoco", "gate_enforced_in_ci": true},
  "uses_testcontainers": true,
  "springboottest_count": 1,
  "forbidden_patterns_found": []
}
]]></code>
  </example>

  <example valid="false">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "module": "billing-service",
  "framework": "junit4",
  "test_classes": [{"name": "user_controller", "layer": "controller", "slice_annotation": "@SpringBootTest", "test_count": 0}],
  "coverage": {"line": 35.0, "branch": 12.0, "tool": "cobertura", "gate_enforced_in_ci": false},
  "uses_testcontainers": false,
  "springboottest_count": 5,
  "forbidden_patterns_found": ["Thread.sleep(1000) in OrdersServiceTest.waitsForJob"]
}
]]></code>
    <note>Wrong framework + naming; slice-controller using @SpringBootTest; H2 instead of Testcontainers; gate off; many @SpringBootTest; Thread.sleep used.</note>
  </example>

  <section title="Forbidden patterns">
    <list>
      <item>`Thread.sleep` inside a test method.</item>
      <item>`H2` / `HSQLDB` for repository tests.</item>
      <item>`@SpringBootTest` used for a controller-only or repository-only slice.</item>
      <item>Mixing Hamcrest + AssertJ + JUnit assertions in the same class.</item>
      <item>Double-mocking (mocking both the service and its repository in a controller test).</item>
    </list>
  </section>

  <reference path="scripts/validate-java-junit-testing.py">Validator script</reference>
</text>
